column2: Cvv
column33: Warner Brothers: Remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2
column34:
It is common knowledge at this point that in the case of Amber Heard vs. Johnny Depp, Amber Heard gaslit everyone around her and painted her victim as the abuser. This has resulted in Depp being all but blacklisted from the movie scene, while Heard has recently been awarded for her actions by being allowed to remain onboard the Aquaman franchise.

While the courts may have allowed her to get away with it, there is no reason that we can't force justice in our own way, by having her removed from the set of Aquaman 2 completely. The fact that she is allowed to continue to make a significant amount of money from filming while still openly bashing her victim is absolutely disgusting, and should not be tolerated in any way, shape, or form.

Sign this petition now to send a message: We will not stand for a documented abuser being allowed to star in a major film while her victim remains blacklisted from the industry!

column33: Warner Brothers: Remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2
column34:
It is common knowledge at this point that in the case of Amber Heard vs. Johnny Depp, Amber Heard gaslit everyone around her and painted her victim as the abuser. This has resulted in Depp being all but blacklisted from the movie scene, while Heard has recently been awarded for her actions by being allowed to remain onboard the Aquaman franchise.

While the courts may have allowed her to get away with it, there is no reason that we can't force justice in our own way, by having her removed from the set of Aquaman 2 completely. column33: Warner Brothers: Remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2
column34:

While the courts may have allowed her to get away with it, there is no reason that we can't force justice in our own way, by having her removed from the set of Aquaman 2 completely. The fact that she is allowed to continue to make a significant amount of money from filming while still openly bashing her victim is absolutely disgusting, and should not be tolerated in any way, shape, or form.

Sign this petition now to send a message: We will not stand for a documented abuser being allowed to star in a major film while her victim remains blacklisted from the industry!

column33: Warner Brothers: Remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2
column34:

column2: Believe it or not I just watched aqua Man for the first time 2 weeks ago, and I really wasn’t drawn to her character, she dulled the scene for me. Trust, she can be replaced there’s plenty out there that can make Aquaman even better! I’m signing this not because of what’s going on in the case because that’s a separate issue and has nothing to do with the movie. But a woman who lies and got caught in her lies and recorded people without their knowledge, setting them up. If that’s not a red flag to ditch her I don’t know what else. If she indeed got into aquaman because Johnny Depp helped her, then because of that reason as well she should be removed. She manipulated, abused, and messed up pirates of the Caribbean for all of us! For her own selfish ways. Remove Heard from aquaman 2 please, because I really really liked the movie. Except her part she made it a bit boring for me.

column22: A Geeky Asian Girl that loves Cats, Iron Man, Nightmare Before Christmas, Daft Punk, Tobey Maguire's Spider-Man
column33: Warner Brothers: Remove Amber Heard from Aquaman 2
column34:
It is common knowledge at this point that in the case of Amber Heard vs. Johnny Depp, Amber Heard gaslit everyone around her and painted her victim as the abuser. This has resulted in Depp being all but blacklisted from the movie scene, while Heard has recently been awarded for her actions by being allowed to remain onboard the Aquaman franchise.

While the courts may have allowed her to get away with it, there is no reason that we can't force justice in our own way, by having her removed from the set of Aquaman 2 completely. The fact that she is allowed to continue to make a significant amount of money from filming while still openly bashing her victim is absolutely disgusting, and should not be tolerated in any way, shape, or form.

Sign this petition now to send a message: We will not stand for a documented abuser being allowed to star in a major film while her victim remains blacklisted from the industry!
